SIMPLE: brocatel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brocatel
<hw>Bro"ca*tel</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>brocatelle</ets>, fr. It. <ets>brocatello</ets>: cf. Sp.
<ets>brocatel</ets>. See <er>Brocade</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
kind of coarse brocade, or figured fabric, used chiefly for tapestry,
linings for carriages, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A marble, clouded and veined with white, gray,
yellow, and red, in which the yellow usually prevails. It is also called
<xex>Siena marble</xex>, from its locality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brocatello</ent>⟦br⟧
